<br>
On fizzles, Atols fizzles more.  BoF has an adjustment of 25 while Atols has an adjustment of 5.  Add in the fact that BoF is a lower level spell, thus the fizzles are less due to the fact your level compared to the level spell you are casting effects fizzle rate.  Oh also for 6 AA points you can make it impossible to fizzle BoF.  You would need another 6 points to make that possible for Atols.<br>
<br>
I have found extra minute duration to be useless to me as I have found I need, on average, 2 and a half minutes to finish a quad from the first nuke so I am recasting both once regardless (Atol's is exactly 2.5 min, but I am not nuking the second it takes hold, thus I still needed a recast.)  The .5 second faster cast time is also of minimum concern.  You shouldn't be cutting it that close because simple things like lag and client prediction have more effect on your quadding ability than .5 sec from a spell cast. <br>
<br>
